\begin_layout Standard
Using the solutions to equations 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:forwardflux"

\end_inset

 for the forward flux, equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:adjointflux"

\end_inset

 for the adjoint flux, then the normalization for the forward flux and normaliza
tion for the adjoint flux, and finally using the spatial distribution for
 both fluxes, we can get the following profiles.
 Assuming that 
\begin_inset Formula $\Sigma_{r1}=\Sigma_{a1}+\Sigma_{s1\rightarrow2}$
\end_inset

 and that 
\begin_inset Formula $\Sigma_{r2}=\Sigma_{a2}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{c}
\varphi_{1}\\
\varphi_{2}
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{c}
0.9909\\
0.1344
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\phi_{0}=0.5127
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{c}
\varphi_{1}^{*}\\
\varphi_{2}^{*}
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{c}
0.8951\\
0.4456
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\phi_{0}^{*}=0.0117
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
